Execute this rule entirely when the user asks to "setup container", "setup environment", "configure environment" or prompts `@setup-environment`. 

The user may call this place with a more specific prompt as well in which case we might need to execute a part of this plan. To do this, first of all look at the instructions under each heading and see which part(s) of the plan need to be executed and then execute them. There are four separate parts of the plan namely: 

* Update settings.json
* Update ~/.bashrc
* Setup signing key
* Get extensions

# Update settings.json

Only execute this part of the plan when the user asks to "update settings", or "update settings.json" and exit. Do not execute the rest of the plan

1. We will be applying edits to this file `/home/coder/.cursor-server/data/Machine/settings.json`
2. Update or add the key `"clangFormat.executable.default"` with the value obtained by running `which clang-format` in a terminal. The value may be: `/home/coder/.conda/envs/rapids/bin/clang-format`

Example of the correct setting:
```json
"clangFormat.executable.default": "/home/coder/.conda/envs/rapids/bin/clang-format",
```

3. If not already then add or edit the following keys `"[cuda-cpp]"`, `"[c]`, and `"[cpp]"` to be like this:
```json
  "[c]": {
    "editor.defaultFormatter": "seaube.clangformat",
    "editor.formatOnSave": true
  },
  "[cpp]": {
    "editor.defaultFormatter": "seaube.clangformat",
    "editor.formatOnSave": true
  },
  "[cuda-cpp]": {
    "editor.defaultFormatter": "seaube.clangformat",
    "editor.formatOnSave": true
  },
```

4. Add or edit the `"[python]"` key to be as follows:
```json
